The paper discusses the measurement and evaluation of mobile network performance, which falls under the category of network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also touches upon the impact of network performance on applications, which could fall under the category of cybersecurity and privacy (cs.CR) or systems and control (cs.SY). The use of tools and services for measurement and evaluation could fall under the category of information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper mentions the need for prototyping mobile applications, which could fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
